{{Infobox figure skater |name= Laurie Hickox |image= |caption= |fullname= Laurie Jean Hickox |altname= Laurie Hickox |country= [[United States]] |birth_date= {{birth date|1945|12|6}} |death_date= {{death date and age|1961|2|15|1945|12|6}} |death_place= [[Berg]]-[[Kampenhout]], [[Vlaams-Brabant]], [[Belgium]] |residence= |height= |coach= |formercoach= [[Edi Scholdan]] |choreographer= |formerchoreographer= |skating club= [[SC of San Francisco]] |retired= }} '''Laurie Jean Hickox''' December 6, 1945 &ndash; February 15, 1961) was an [[United States|American]] [[pair skater]] who competed with her brother [[William Hickox]]. They won the bronze medal at the [[1961 United States Figure Skating Championships|U.S. Championships]], earning them the right to compete a month later at the [[World Figure Skating Championships|World Championships]] in [[Prague]]. They also finished sixth at the [[North American Figure Skating Championships]] that year. They died along with their teammates on February 15, 1961 when [[Sabena Flight 548]] crashed near Brussels, Belgium en route to the World Championships. She was 15 years old.
